			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1460877">
									

<p>Thus the mention of &quot;paying penance to the Church&quot; - this story is set in the days when one could still buy indulgences for sins not yet committed. In any event, saying that they ended up &quot;in Christ's embrace&quot; is more of a metaphorical statement than anything else - even in a gory, old-fashioned fairy tale where the main characters die at the end, you can't very well close by saying they're in Hell. :)</p>

